description.narrative: More out-of-school children, especially girls, and those in the most vulnerable situations, access quality pre-primary, primary and alternative learning opportunities., which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Learning Outcomes, Skills Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, more children have access to early stimulation and quality basic education and learning in inclusive and safe school environments.

title.narrative: More out-of-school children, especially girls, and those in the most vulnerable situations, access quality pre-primary, primary and alternative learning opportunities.

description.narrative: Despite instability, insecurity and economic challenges caused by civil protests in Sudan, out of the 2.9 million OOSC (6-13 year olds), 177,082 (49.5% girls) were supported by UNICEF and enrolled in schools and alternative learning programs, including 52,717 children affected by emergency situations. 45% or 80,008 OOSC were enrolled in Alternative Learning Programs (ALPs) while the other 55% have been enrolled in basic schools. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2019
